    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix scheduling priority inversion in M2AP message handling\n\n### Summary\nThe M2AP decoder was experiencing scheduling priority inversion where lower-priority traffic was being served before higher-priority downstream of function `m2ap_decode_pdu`. This was caused by incorrect indexing into callback handler matrices using raw procedure code values instead of mapped indices.\n\nThe issue occurred because procedure codes are not guaranteed to be sequential integers starting from 0, leading to incorrect handler selection and processing order.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/M2AP/m2ap_eNB_handler.c`: Added procedure code to index mapping function and updated handler lookup\n- `openair2/M2AP/m2ap_handler.c`: Added procedure code to index mapping function and updated handler lookup  \n- `openair2/M2AP/m2ap_MCE_handler.c`: Added procedure code to index mapping function and updated handler lookup\n\nUnder high M2AP message load, this could cause MBMS session start requests to be delayed behind lower priority M2 setup responses, leading to service disruption for multicast users.\n"
}